Bromus carinatus

   [3912.jpg]
    Authority   Hook. & Arn.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3912

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A deep rooted grass with a good leafy growth and
   culms up to 50-100 cm tall. USES Grown for forage. GROWING PERIOD
   Annual, biennial, or short-lived perennial. COMMON NAMES Mountain
   brome, California brome grass. FURTHER INF Mountain brome is common on
   open ground and in lightly wooded areas of the western United States.

   Sources
   SOURCES (B. carinatus Hook. & Arn.)
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 147 [USE, LIG]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Heath M 1985 pp 205 [USE, DEP]
   Kernick M 1961 pp 38 [PHO]

